## Bash code for NER using Stanford NER (3.5.2). The "taggedEntities" doesn't seem to be recognized anymore, but "slashTags"
    will give you the same result--just need to tweak the last bit of R code to get the Person-tag document-term matrix to account for
    the */ rather than the <*>...</*> format. You may also need to run the -echo- command multiple times--perhaps with the docs spread 
    out over multiple folders--as it seems to max out before it tags all 280 documents. Same goes for the actual NER code 
    (starting on line 9): simply disperse the content of the "docs" folder over multiple folders and batch tag the contens of each 
    folder separately. ##

$ cd /Users/stanford-ner-2015-04-20/docs
$ echo “unique_identifier” | tee -a *.txt
$ cd /Users/stanford-ner-2015-12-09/
$ java -mx600m -cp stanford-ner.jar:lib/* edu.stanford.nlp.ie.crf.CRFClassifier 
      -loadClassifier /Users/mat4a/stanford-ner-2015-04-20/classifiers/english.all.3class.distsim.crf.ser.gz 
      -outputFormat taggedEntities -textFiles docs/*.txt > tagged_text.txt
$ csplit -f tags tagged_text.txt /unique_identifier/ {280}
